    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plastics forming process in which a granular, powdered, or liquid plastic is introduced into a mold which is closed and rotated horizontally and vertically. The plastic is forced against the walls of the mold.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011611/Dietz, Plastics Terminology (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proceso de formado de plásticos en el cual un plástico granular, en polvo o líquido es introducido en un molde cerrado con rotación horizontal y vertical. El plástico es forzado contra las paredes del molde.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vormingsproces voor plastic waarbij een korrelig, verpoederd of vloeibaar plastic in een afgesloten gietvorm wordt gegoten die zowel horizontaal als verticaal wordt geroteerd. Het plastic wordt dan tegen de wanden van de vorm geperst.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>塑膠成型的過程，將顆粒狀、粉狀或液狀的塑膠注入封閉且水平、垂直旋轉的模具中；塑膠佈滿模具內壁。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
